    the practice of bonus payment as a periodical payment could be said to have begun during the first world war when the  industries  made  huge  profits    the  government  of  india  appointed  a  bonus commission on december 16 1961  in one its recommendations the then bonus commission said that 60 per cent of the available surplus should be distributed as bonus  but still this has not been implemented in the case of industries  this is our humble request to the minister that there should not be any ceiling    